  "name": "Anti-Insulating Muscle Fibers",
  "type": "feat",
  "_id": "UbMGJdRyzw5Uwm1T",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Tsukizuma.PNG",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your Muscles are so packed with electricity, it can be seen leaking off you whenever you move, and you can weaponize this. Creatures you deal unarmed damage too, or fail a saving throw caused by a Taijustu you cast, are <em>Ionized</em> until the start of your next turn. All instances of Unarmed damage dealt to <em>Ionized</em> Creatures are treated as Lighting Damage for the purposes of overcoming resistances and damage reduction, and deal an additional 1d6 Lightning Damage. This becomes 2d6 at 7th level, and 3d6 at 15th Level</p><p>Starting at 3rd Level, You gain a +1 AC to your AC for every 35 ft you move each turn, until the start of your next turn. Max Bonus is equal to 1/2 your Proficiency Bonus (Rounded Down).</p><p>Starting at 11th Level, increase your Crit range when targeting <em>Ionized</em> Creatures by +1, and you may replace any Condition caused by a Taijutsu you cast against an <em>Ionised</em> Creature, with an equal amount of the <em>Shocked</em> Condition</p><p></p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
